        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 22 at 5:40AM EDT until June 22 at 6:15AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 540 AM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from East Freetown to near Smithville Flats to near Sidney
to near Bovina Center, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Oneonta, Norwich, Sidney, Walton, Delhi, Guilford, Roxbury,
Colchester, Kortright, and Coventry.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Heavy rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to flash
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
